        <p class="rdimg"><img src="/Risks/assets/images/rdigest.png" alt="The Risks Digest"/></p>
    <h1 class="rdigest">The RISKS Digest</h1>
    <h1 class="cntr">Forum on Risks to the Public in Computers and Related Systems</h1>
    <h2 class="cntr">
	<i><a href="//www.acm.org">ACM</a> Committee on Computers and Public Policy,
	<a href="http://www.csl.sri.com/neumann/neumann.html">Peter G. Neumann</a>, moderator</i>
    </h2>
    <h2 class="cntr">Volume 31 Issue 10</h2>
        <h2 class="cntr">Thursday 7 March 2019</h2><h2>Contents</h2><dl>
<dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
<a href="#subj1">All Intel chips open to new Spoiler non-Spectre attack: Don't expect a  quick fix.</a></dt>
<dd><a href="#subj1.1">ZDNet</a><br/>
</dd><dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
<a href="#subj2">The rise of the online ticketing bots</a></dt>
<dd><a href="#subj2.1">David Strom</a><br/>
</dd><dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
<a href="#subj3">DeepFake litigation</a></dt>
<dd><a href="#subj3.1">Fortune</a><br/>
</dd><dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
<a href="#subj4">Fake paid product reviews on Amazon challenged</a></dt>
<dd><a href="#subj4.1">Consumer Health</a><br/>
</dd><dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
<a href="#subj5">Siri, What Should I Eat?</a></dt>
<dd><a href="#subj5.1">Cell.com</a><br/>
</dd><dt><i class="circle fas fa-circle"></i>
