<h3 class="ht"><a id="subj1.1" name="subj1.1" href="#subj1.1"><i class="flash fas fa-bolt"></i></a>All Intel chips open to new Spoiler non-Spectre attack: Don't expect a quick fix.  (ZDNet)</h3>
<address>
Monty Solomon 
&lt;monty@roscom.com&gt;
</address>
<i>Tue, 5 Mar 2019 13:42:38 -0500</i><pre>
<a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/all-intel-chips-open-to-new-spoiler-non-spectre-attack-dont-expect-a-quick-fix/">https://www.zdnet.com/article/all-intel-chips-open-to-new-spoiler-non-spectre-attack-dont-expect-a-quick-fix/</a>

Intel CPUs afflicted with simple data-spewing spec-exec vulnerability
